Open Letter to former Macalester President Brian Rosenberg

Talk a bit about your background PERIOD You are a Macalester grad correct

Yes PERIOD I will try to give you the more entertaining things PERIOD I grew up in Kansas mostly around Kansas City PERIOD I left high school when I was  came here Macalester when I was  PERIOD So thats kind of interesting I was very young when I came here PERIOD I was actually looking at Dartmouth and I just found Macalester PERIOD I have a long involved story about how I was going to go to Carletonthe criteria I used to select my college was ridiculous PERIOD I didnt go to Carleton because the guy who showed me around campus had tape on his glasses right there touching the bridge of his glasses and the admissions guy at Dartmouth was wearing white socks PERIOD laughs I mean it was just completely ridiculous why I had chosen to come here PERIOD

What were you involved with during your time here

When I was here I had a great time PERIOD I was very involved PERIOD I was an RA I was a dorm president I was on Program Board I ran for President PERIOD If you look back in The Mac Weekly for spring of  I think there is a picture of me with long hair running for president PERIOD I majored in Math and Chemistry PERIOD And I was profoundly influenced by Professor Konhauser in the math department PERIOD I came thinking I was going to be chemistry and probably premed PERIOD And I had a great experience in the chemistry department but Dr PERIOD Konhauser really took an interest in me and helped me PERIOD I mean I really think I knew I was interested in teaching and education from the time I was  but he really helped PERIOD He was the person who started the problem of the week and was just a real inspiration to me PERIOD

What about postgrad

I got hired at St PERIOD Paul Academy the private school about six blocks away the day after I graduated from college PERIOD With no interview no resume somebody walked by and saw me tutoring someone and said Do you want to work here And I had been there ever since PERIOD I took a couple years off to teach in the Netherlands and took a sabbatical year to teach in a rural school in Jamaica PERIOD But other than that I have been all of six blocks away PERIOD

Fun fact post grad I lived in a house with a bunch of other Macalester graduates and we formed a really bad punk rock band and became very popular as sort of a comic relief PERIOD We warmed up some pretty well known bands The Replacements and things like that PERIOD But we were just horrible PERIOD Laughs I think WMCN might have a copy of our single PERIOD

What was the name of your band

The Tuff Bunnies PERIOD

Werent you in a movie too

Oh yeah PERIOD  I was the bailiff in a movie called Justice. im on IMDB The movie was written and funded by a small law firm in Minneapolis that specialized in civil rights litigation PERIOD  Apparently the four lawyers in the firm got a large settlement and decided making a movie would a nice break from the law business PERIOD  One of the lawyers wrote the screenplay they all served as producers PERIOD  They hired a few professional Hollywood actors and used local talent for the rest of the cast PERIOD As the bailiff Im on screen for about three seconds PERIOD I actually cant believe I got a credit but apparently being the former math teacher of one of the producers gets you on a leg up in the movie biz PERIOD  And the funny thing about me getting to be the bailiff was that I was just supposed to be a juror but when the actor showed up for the bailiffs role he was too large to fit into the uniform  We filmed at the courthouse in St PERIOD Paul PERIOD  Being dressed in a cops uniform complete with phony gun at the courthouse was a blast PERIOD  Everybody thought I was a real cop and asked me all kinds of questions PERIOD  I was tempted to go out and hassle random passersby but thought better of it PERIOD Theres my movie career in a nutshell PERIOD

Where did you go to grad school

I did some parttime grad school work at the U of M and then I went to Harvard and got my Masters in Education in  PERIOD And then I came back here for a couple of years and then it was  when I was in the Netherlands PERIOD And then  was when I was in Jamaica PERIOD And now Im here PERIOD And that was really kind PERIOD I got an email from Macalester last summer asking if I was interested in being a visiting professor and its been exciting PERIOD And now I have just taken a job in Madagascar for next year so I will be moving there PERIOD

What did you do in the Netherlands

I taught at the American school of the Hague PERIOD I taught high school math PERIOD

Different styles of teaching there

Id say the only thing is that the students and parents are much more used to travel PERIOD If I tried to take some kids to downtown Minneapolis from St PERIOD Paul Academy their parents would be all worried about them PERIOD And there we took kids and flew them to London and said Come back in eight hours well be at the train station Students there just grow up that way PERIOD

What did you do in Jamaica

Since  I have been taking computers to Jamaican schools PERIOD I run a little nonprofit Little World Schoolhouse PERIOD We actually just sent  laptop computers down there which is the first time we have done that in a little while PERIOD I was very active in the 90s when companies were turning over computers and I would go set them up at some schools down there with some friends of mine PERIOD And that got me interested in spending some more time down there PERIOD So I went to teach at a school called York Castle High School up in a rural area called Brownstown PERIOD I set up a computer lab for them and was working in the computer lab with the computer teacher PERIOD Then they had a math teacher who got sick so I did part of the year teaching a math class PERIOD I lived in a house with a couple of Jamaican guys and it was a great experience PERIOD I still love the place and I still am involved going down there PERIOD

What are you going to do in Madagascar

I am going to be teaching at the American school of Antananarivo PERIOD My significant other is there already teaching fourth grade PERIOD So I went there and visited over the break and its a spectacular place so I am really looking forward to it PERIOD At this point we are thinking well be there a couple of years but well see PERIOD Its a little school but its charming and its growing and they need math and science teachers and its in Madagascar laughs

What has it been like coming back to Macalester

The other math professors are so welcoming and entertaining and engaging PERIOD They are just fun people PERIOD Some of the meetings are laughoutloud funny PERIOD I felt very fortunate that way PERIOD Its funny that there are still professors here from when I was here PERIOD I am right next door to Dr PERIOD Roberts who I had as a professor and Martin Gunderson is here PERIOD I think I was in his very first class he ever taught here PERIOD And then the students I think its hard to compare PERIOD In many ways they are the same PERIOD I see the students here now maybe being a little more affected by the financial issues in the world and being a little more concerned PERIOD They just cant frolic the way people were frolicking when I was going to college PERIOD laughs People were no longer worried about the draft and times were good and a lot of people were maybe having a little too much fun at Macalester PERIOD laughs Im still impressed by Macalesters commitment to internationalism and social causes Im heartened PERIOD I want to write a little piece for the alumni magazine to say Its still the place you know and love. did Mac influence your life path

I would say very much so PERIOD I think I was incredibly happy at Mac because I thrived academically which I had not in high school and was positively influenced by the ethos here the concern for world issues and social justice PERIOD I think I really developed in that direction a long way PERIOD

Favorite thing about teaching

Its two fold PERIOD I really do enjoy mathematics PERIOD I think thats where Dr PERIOD Konhauser influenced me PERIOD Instead of being the Peanuts wah wah wah voice at the board I would want somebody to think Oh wow thats pretty cool

Its like doing puzzles PERIOD People do puzzles for fun I hope people enjoy math in the same way PERIOD But I also enjoy what I would call the pastoral side PERIOD Especially when you are working with junior highaged kids to shepherd them through those rough waters and then see them on the other end develop into selfcontained human beings that are interested in doing good in the world PERIOD

Favorite part of math

Problem solving PERIOD Whenever I am teaching I try to find problems that will really engage people PERIOD It all started with the problem of the week here PERIOD That kind of puzzle problem is what really motivates me PERIOD

Plans for the future

I am looking forward to the teaching adventure ahead PERIOD But I still want to hit the big time in the world of rock and roll PERIOD laughs I still play every week PERIOD As a fun fact Willie Gambucci who was a theater major and graduated from Mac last spring I taught him in high school and played in his high school band PERIOD We put out a CD you can listen to it on Spotify PERIOD laughs I still really enjoy music PERIOD I know it will never go anywhere PERIOD But its keeping me occupied PERIOD I actually play on Friday nights with some people that are Mac grads PERIOD Which is the nice thing about Macalester being in the Twin Cities PERIOD I think theres a funny name like the one mile club for people who never go too far PERIOD But I still socialize and see a lot of my Macalester classmates PERIOD

Any other things you want to throw out to the community

I sang with Earth Wind and Fire laughs We Leiter and partner were at a charity auction and someone else paid thousands of dollars to sing with Earth Wind and Fire and we were saying to them Oh thats so cool that you did that. and then they said to us We dont want to do it we want to watch you do it. and we went Okay we will So we got to get up and sing with Earth Wind and Fire at the convention center last May PERIOD

Another random thing is that Steven Levitt the author of Freakonomics is a former student of mine and we are pretty close PERIOD Actually if you go to the Freakonomics podcasts I did an interview at the Fitzgerald Theater about his life and then we did a quiz bowl match and I am moderating PERIOD

The Student News Site of Macalester College
